The first time he saw her, it was love at first sight. Unfortunately for Sorata Kanda, "she" was a cat named Hikari and his school's rules forbid keeping pets in the regular dorms. As a result, Sorata is banished to the infamous Sakura Hall alongside other troublesome and unusual students like Jin, overzealous playboy, Ryuunosuke, the reclusive hermit, and Mashiro, a brilliant artist who's so unfocused and clueless about the real world that dorm supervisor Ms. Sengoku assigns Sorata the task of taking care of her along with his ever-growing collection of stray cats!
(Source: Sentai Filmworks)
Sekai Saikou no Ansatsusha, Isekai Kizoku ni Tensei suru
Action, Adventure, Drama, Fantasy, Mystery, Romance

The world's number one assassin has been reincarnated as the eldest son of a family of aristocrat assassins. In exchange for being reincarnated in another world, a goddess has imposed upon him one condition. "Kill the Hero who is prophesied to destroy the world."
This was to be the mission in his new life. The synergistic effect of the vast knowledge and experience he gained that made all manner of assassinations possible in the modern world, and the secret techniques and magic of the fantasy world's most powerful family of assassins turn him into the greatest assassin of all time.
(Source: Crunchyroll)
Isshou Hatarakitakunai Ore ga Classmate no Daininki Idol ni Natsukaretara

Rintaro Shido, a high school boy who aspires to be a full-time house-husband, is in the same class as Rei Otosaki, the center of the popular idol group "Millefeuille Stars." The two have never been involved with each other, until one day when Rei nearly collapses from hunger, and Rintaro makes a home-cooked meal to feed her.......

"I'll pay you 300,000-yen a month. Can I come and eat with you every day?"

Thus began their new relationship, almost like a couple living together. Rintaro is unable to grasp the proper distance between himself and Rei, who comes to his room where he lives alone. There, Rei shows a vulnerable side that she would never show in the classroom or on stage.......?

This is the start of a romantic comedy about a semi-cohabitation arrangement with a beautiful, popular idol girl, that will make your heart tingle and pound!

(Source: Over-Lap, translated)

He and she were enemies. Until he knew he had the same loneliness in a dichotomized world. They are cheap, strong, and never die. The ultimate life regeneration system "Arcadia" was born from teenage soldiers who fight by making full use of the complex regeneration <Respawn>. They were invincible boys and girls (children who transcended death) who died on the battlefield and revived. The forefront of the war in which the two great powers compete for hegemony. Akihito, a boy who leads a platoon as an ace of the United States Army, is ordered to collect confidential information that is inevitable to be wiped out because of his poor performance. However, Akihito, who has kept his companions in an unexpected battle and collapse, is isolated deep underground where complex regeneration <respawn> is impossible, along with his fateful nemesis, the elite girl Philia of the Federal Army. Two people who have opposite personalities and skills and have the worst compatibility will cooperate and aim to return to the ground. The story of the encounter and resonance between him and her who continued to die on the battlefield that never died begins!
<i>Notes: - Winner of the Gold Award in the 28thDengeki Novel Prize.
